body:
The example below is preventing ~40% of the UVM-next tests from executing, they stop at the error:

`UVM_FATAL src/base/uvm_phase_hopper.svh(590) @ 9200000000000000: reporter [PH_TIMEOUT] Default timeout of 9200000000000000 hit, indicating a probable testbench issue`

This appears due to uvm.uvm_sched.pre_reset never completing.  This is because wait_for_nba_region looses a wait after being called twice:

```
  task uvm_wait_for_nba_region;
    static int nba;
    static int next_nba;
    automatic int caller;
    next_nba++;
    caller = next_nba;
    `DBGF(("uvm_wait_for_nba_region prep next_nba was=%0d  nba=%0d", next_nba, nba));
    nba <= next_nba;
    `DBGF(("uvm_wait_for_nba_region @(nba) wait was=%0d  nba=%0d caller=%0d", next_nba, nba, caller));
    @(nba);   // Works: #0
    `DBGF(("uvm_wait_for_nba_region @(nba) did was=%0d  nba=%0d caller=%0d", next_nba, nba, caller));
  endtask


