If I instead use `#0` it works, but that's not equivalent of course. You can select that in UVM with the ifdef's `-DUVM_NO_WAIT_FOR_NBA -DUVM_POUND_ZERO_COUNT=2`.

Attempting to reduce this to an example:

<details><summary>Example</summary>

```
// verilog_format: off
`define stop $stop
`define checkd(gotv,expv) do if ((gotv) !== (expv)) begin $write("%%Error: %s:%0d:  got=%0d exp=%0d\n", `__FILE__,`__LINE__, (gotv), (expv)); `stop; end while(0);
// verilog_format: on

`ifdef TEST_VERBOSE
 `define DISPLAY_VERBOSE(msg) do $display msg; while(0)
`else
 `define DISPLAY_VERBOSE(msg) do ; while(0)
`endif

// v---- FIXME note this
// verilator lint_off INITIALDLY

package pkg;
  // Task taken from UVM
  task wait_for_nba_region;
    static int nba;
    static int next_nba;
    automatic int caller;

    `DISPLAY_VERBOSE(("wait_for_nba_region prep was=%0d  nba=%0d", next_nba, nba));
    next_nba++;
    caller = next_nba;
    `DISPLAY_VERBOSE(("wait_for_nba_region pre-assign was=%0d  nba=%0d caller=%0d", next_nba, nba, caller));
    nba <= next_nba;
    `DISPLAY_VERBOSE(("wait_for_nba_region @(nba) wait was=%0d  nba=%0d caller=%0d", next_nba, nba, caller));
    @(nba);
    `DISPLAY_VERBOSE(("wait_for_nba_region @(nba) did was=%0d  nba=%0d caller=%0d", next_nba, nba, caller));
  endtask
endpackage

module t;
  int got[int];

  task automatic wait_and_set(input int id);
    `DISPLAY_VERBOSE(("wait_and_set(%0d) start", id));
    pkg::wait_for_nba_region();
    `DISPLAY_VERBOSE(("wait_and_set(%0d) end", id));
    got[id] = id;
    `DISPLAY_VERBOSE(("set[%0d]=%0d", id, got[id]));
  endtask

  initial begin
    #1;
    `DISPLAY_VERBOSE(("fork"));
    fork
      wait_and_set(1);
      wait_and_set(2);
      wait_and_set(3);
    join_none
    `DISPLAY_VERBOSE(("join_none done"));
    `checkd(got[1], 0);
    `checkd(got[2], 0);
    `checkd(got[3], 0);

    #1;
    `DISPLAY_VERBOSE(("check"));
    `checkd(got[1], 1);
    `checkd(got[2], 2);
    `checkd(got[3], 3);

    $write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
    $finish;
  end
endmodule
```
</details>

I realize INITIALDLY is not supported but it seems mostly working (at least one pass and in the t_assigndly_dynamic test).

With the above test I get:

`%Error: t/t_assigndly_dynamic2.v:34: Null pointer dereferenced`

It's due to this C++ code:

```
vlSelfRef.__Vtrigprevexpr_h20582dca__0
        = VL_NULL_CHECK(vlSelfRef.__Vtask_wait_for_nba_region__4____VDynScope_wait_for_nba_region_0, "t/t_assigndly_dynamic2.v", 34)
        ->__PVT__nba;
```

I suspect with that fixed we will see the issue of wrong wakeup.

@kbieganski, might you look into this (after break)?

